3.Cannot SSH or RDP to an Azure VM, How will you fix it?
A. I’ll check VM status and NSG rules, port 22 open, window 3389 open, instances configured with public IP, VM is up and running due to resources. 
SSH keys user using, even authorize to do ssh.
I use Azure Network Watcher, reset credentials, or recover the VM using Serial Console or disk attach.
4.Azure Function failed to execute. How do you debug?
A. I will head to the application insights to check the logs to see then I will head to function timeout. Users configure less timeout such as five seconds, 10s and occasionally function takes a lot of time. I will ask the developer, I will also look at memory limit because function consumes more memory. I will take the help from the development team why function is occasionally taking more memory than the configured threshold. So I will try to check the environment variables as well as the keys. Finally,  Azure Functions it also supports live metrics. So I will take a look at live metrics by performing a test run. 
